   "source": [
    "# Fourier Masking"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "from imagemks.rw import listload\n",
    "from imagemks.masking import maskfourier\n",
    "from imagemks.structures import donut, wheel"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading a Microstructure Image"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "path_to_data = '/home/sven/Projects/ImageMKS/examples/figs/'\n",
    "loader = listload(path_to_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "A = loader[0].crop(box=(0,0,301,301))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A = np.array(A)\n",
    "A = A[:,:,0]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7,7))\n",
    "plt.imshow(A, cmap='gray')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Masks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1008x1008 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mask_x = np.zeros(A.shape).astype(np.bool_)\n",
    "mask_x[A.shape[0]//2,:] = True\n",
    "mask_y = np.zeros(A.shape).astype(np.bool_)\n",
    "mask_y[:,A.shape[0]//2] = True\n",
    "\n",
    "mask_wheel = wheel(20, 1, size=A.shape)\n",
    "mask_donut = donut(40,5, size=A.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(14,14))\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (ax, im) in enumerate(zip(axs.ravel(), (mask_x, mask_y, mask_wheel, mask_donut))):\n",
    "    ax.imshow(im, cmap='gray')\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## X Frequency Mask\n",
    "\n",
    "The image on the left shows the intensity changes along the x direction."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A_in, A_out = maskfourier(A, mask_x)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,6))\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[0].imshow(A_in, cmap='gray')\n",
    "axs[0].set_title('Using frequencies in the mask')\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].imshow(A_out, cmap='gray')\n",
    "axs[1].set_title('Using frequencies outside the mask')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "\n",
